  "algorithm_summary": "The Coronary Heart Disease phenotype algorithm identifies cases through two pathways: CASE 1 requires 2 or more ICD-9 codes for myocardial infarction (410.*, 412.*, 429.7*) or obstructive coronary artery disease (411.*, 413.*, 414.*, V45.81, V45.82) on separate days, occurring on the same date as specific outpatient encounter CPT codes, with patients \u226530 years old during the qualification period (1/1/2009-present). CASE 2 requires 1 or more ICD-9 or CPT procedure codes for revascularization/cardiothoracic surgery with the same age and time period requirements. The algorithm excludes deceased patients, those with unknown sex, and patients discharged to hospice care.",
